23
00:02:09,583 --> 00:02:11,291
<i>- Way to be off tempo.</i>
- [growls]

24
00:02:11,375 --> 00:02:12,583
- You know this song is new
to me, right?

25
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:14,958
<i>- What I know is that</i>
<i>you're being lazy!</i>

26
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:16,625
<i>The etude needs work, too!</i>

27
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:17,916
<i>It's overtime,</i>
<i>Friend A!</i>

28
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
<i>Start freaking out already!</i>

29
00:02:19,083 --> 00:02:20,000
- Hold on a second!

30
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:21,583
You're trying to freak me out?

31
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:23,458
<i>- Oh, maybe you shouldn't</i>
<i>have wasted</i>

32
00:02:23,541 --> 00:02:25,291
<i>what little time you have</i>
<i>flirting with that first year!</i>

33
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:26,416
- How the hell was I flirting?

34
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,750
- Wow, it's like
she's right here.

35
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:28,791
- Hope he's got a lot
of minutes.

36
00:02:28,875 --> 00:02:30,250
[phone beeps]

37
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:31,208
- Butt head.

38
00:02:31,291 --> 00:02:32,458
- Hi, Kaori.
Are you ready to go?

39
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:33,583
- Already?

40
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:35,833
I lost track of the time.

41
00:02:35,916 --> 00:02:37,000
[grunts]

42
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:39,583
[indistinct chatter]

43
00:02:39,666 --> 00:02:41,250
- Man, I only got a C.

44
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:43,416
- Guess I'll try
an easier school.

45
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,708
- Hey, Tsubaki,

46
00:02:44,791 --> 00:02:46,333
how did you do
on the practice test?

47
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:47,083
- [snickers]

48
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:50,250
[chuckles confidently]

49
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:51,375
Read them and weep!

50
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:52,625
[scoffs]

51
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:53,875
- Softball-for-brains got a B?

52
00:02:53,958 --> 00:02:55,416
- Wake up, self.
Wake up!

53
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,083
- I only asked 'cause I thought
I did way better!

54
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:58,166
- You're not Tsubaki!

55
00:02:58,250 --> 00:02:59,875
- [laughing]

56
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:02,416
Bow before me.
Yes, bow to my genius!

57
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:04,500
[laughing]

58
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:05,291
- You love him.
- [grunts]

59
00:03:08,916 --> 00:03:12,666
[distant piano music playing]

60
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:20,250
♪♪

61
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:29,375
- Not here?

62
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:31,583
She gives me all that crap
for not visiting,

63
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:32,916
and then she no-shows?

64
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:37,166
<i>Unless they moved her</i>
<i>'cause she got worse.</i>

65
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,166
What do I do?

66
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:38,833
Should I wait around for her?

67
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:41,458
Or ask the nurse, maybe?

68
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:44,208
- Small world, huh, Arima?
- [screaming]

69
00:03:44,291 --> 00:03:45,583
[grunts]

70
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:46,666
[gasps]

71
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:47,583
Mr. and Mrs. Miyazono!

72
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:50,208
You startled me.

73
00:03:50,291 --> 00:03:52,041
It's good to see you again.

74
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:54,333
- You're here to pay Kaori
a visit,

75
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:55,875
am I right?
- Aww!

76
00:03:55,958 --> 00:03:59,541
- I tried but she wasn't
in her room just now so...

77
00:03:59,625 --> 00:04:01,208
both: Ah!

78
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:04,208
- Come on.
I know where she might be.

79
00:04:06,375 --> 00:04:09,000
- [grunting]

80
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:11,750
[breathing heavily]
- Nice and easy now.

81
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,750
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

82
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:18,083
- She told me she can't afford
to let her muscles atrophy.

83
00:04:18,166 --> 00:04:19,458
She needs her strength

84
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:21,708
so she can play
on stage one more time.

85
00:04:21,791 --> 00:04:24,458
- [breathing heavily]

86
00:04:24,541 --> 00:04:25,583
[grunting]

87
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,750
- You're overdoing it, Kaori.

88
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:28,666
You've gotta pace yourself.

89
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:31,083
- So what if I fall?

90
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:32,916
Violinists are way tougher
than we look.

91
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,291
Bring it on!
[laughing]

92
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:38,250
- This is all thanks to you.
- Hmm?

93
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:42,250
- She'd given up on
most everything, really.

94
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:44,541
Would you look at her now?

95
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:47,833
She's putting her soul
into every step.

96
00:04:48,666 --> 00:04:51,916
- But I haven't done anything.

97
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:52,750
- [exhales]

98
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:56,375
Haven't you?

99
00:04:56,458 --> 00:04:58,041
She's watched you.

100
00:04:58,125 --> 00:05:01,416
Watched you put your heart
and soul into music.

101
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,958
<i>That devotion struck</i>
<i>a chord with her,</i>

102
00:05:04,041 --> 00:05:07,458
<i>deep within Kaori's heart.</i>

103
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:11,708
- The surgery,
I want to have it.

104
00:05:11,791 --> 00:05:14,875
Even if it only gives me
a little more time,

105
00:05:14,958 --> 00:05:15,625
so long as there's
the slightest chance

106
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:17,958
of this working,

107
00:05:18,041 --> 00:05:20,583
I'll grab it as tight as I can.

108
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:22,291
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

109
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:26,208
There's this boy I met back
in April, you see.

110
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:30,458
He was crippled with doubt,
but he was brave for my sake.

111
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:34,625
<i>We played and he shined</i>
<i>like a star out there.</i>

112
00:05:34,708 --> 00:05:36,000
<i>In that moment,</i>

113
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:39,833
<i>I knew I wanted</i>
<i>to bolster that light.</i>

114
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:43,791
I made him a promise,
that doubting boy.

115
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:46,666
I promised we'd play again.

116
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,958
That's why I'm stubborn.

117
00:05:48,041 --> 00:05:51,750
<i>That's why I'm risking it all</i>
<i>on the surgery.</i>

118
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:55,791
<i>'Cause even if the odds</i>
<i>are a million to one,</i>

119
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:58,000
<i>I'm gonna fight,</i>
<i>fight it tooth and nail,</i>

120
00:05:58,083 --> 00:06:01,791
<i>like there's no tomorrow,</i>

121
00:06:01,875 --> 00:06:05,916
<i>'cause that's</i>
<i>what musicians do.</i>

122
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,125
There's plenty of times
I'm scared and sad,

123
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:10,250
but if I just gave up on life
and faded away,

124
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,500
what kind of daughter
would I be?

125
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:18,250
- [crying]

126
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:20,875
- It's the only life I've got,

127
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:24,041
and long or short,
it's mine.

128
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,875
Better make it count, huh?

129
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:32,708
- You've given her something
to fight for, Arima.

130
00:06:32,791 --> 00:06:35,375
<i>My daughter's heart had faded</i>
<i>to gray,</i>

131
00:06:35,458 --> 00:06:38,625
<i>and you brought</i>
<i>the color back.</i>

132
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:40,916
So don't tell me
you did nothing.

133
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,333
Don't you dare, Kousei.

134
00:06:46,166 --> 00:06:48,208
<i>- He's been playing the piano</i>
<i>late at night.</i>

135
00:06:48,291 --> 00:06:49,375
<i>Sometimes all night.</i>

136
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:52,833
I know that competition
is coming up soon,

137
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:54,833
but he's been nonstop since
the festival.

138
00:06:54,916 --> 00:06:56,958
He's gonna burn out.

139
00:06:57,041 --> 00:07:00,083
Not to mention he'll bomb
his entrance exam.

140
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:01,625
- He's focusing
on the right thing,

141
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:02,708
if you ask me.

142
00:07:02,791 --> 00:07:03,875
- Huh?

143
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:04,875
- Think about it.

144
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:07,000
He's trying to get into
a music program.

145
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:08,416
Yeah, they're gonna test him
on the regular junk,

146
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:12,250
but really they're just
looking
at the piano.

147
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:13,750
They're gonna take
the applicants who've done

148
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:16,750
the best at competitions.
It's all about street cred.

149
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,458
And since Arima's been out
of the scene

150
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:20,291
for the last couple of years,

151
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:22,708
he's hurting
in the street cred department.

152
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:24,416
What do you do?

153
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,833
Enter the Eastern Japan
Piano Competition, of course.

154
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:31,083
<i>It's been around forever,</i>
<i>and it's a really big deal.</i>

155
00:07:31,166 --> 00:07:33,208
<i>For schools like</i>
<i>the one Arima's looking at,</i>

156
00:07:33,291 --> 00:07:35,750
<i>letting in the top performers</i>
<i>helps them maintain</i>

157
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,416
<i>that elite image.</i>

158
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:38,750
In other words,

159
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,541
Kousei kicking ass
at this competition

160
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:42,791
is just as good
for him as acing

161
00:07:42,875 --> 00:07:45,458
a regular entrance exam
would be for you or me.

162
00:07:45,541 --> 00:07:48,625
Like he's hitting a home run
with a piano.

163
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:52,500
Stop being so jealous of music
and root for the guy a little.

164
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:54,666
- Who says I'm jealous?

165
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,375
- Better he get
into that school

166
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:58,458
than head overseas, right?

167
00:07:58,541 --> 00:07:59,833
- [grunts]

168
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:03,791
<i>This might be my only chance</i>
<i>to spend time with him.</i>

169
00:08:03,875 --> 00:08:06,791
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

170
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:10,333
- Anyway, I bet you he's wiped
out from these all-nighters.

171
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:12,000
If only some helpful
neighbor girl

172
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:14,625
would bring the guy a snack.

173
00:08:14,708 --> 00:08:16,166
- [grunts]

174
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:21,875
[footsteps]
W--whatever.

175
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:25,291
It's not like I'm doing this
'cause Kashiwagi told me to.

176
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:27,750
Kousei?

177
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:30,041
[screams]

178
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,875
Speak to me!
- Oh, hey.

179
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:32,666
What's up?

180
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:35,375
I dreamt a gorilla got me.

181
00:08:35,458 --> 00:08:39,125
- I thought you were dead,
you dumbass!

182
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:41,500
You've been practicing nonstop.

183
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:42,333
Don't you think
you're overdoing it?

184
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:44,583
- The Bach piece we have
to play,

185
00:08:44,666 --> 00:08:46,458
it's mocking me.
- [grunts]

186
00:08:46,541 --> 00:08:48,208
Well, the sheet music's
on the floor.

187
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:49,833
That might be part of it.

188
00:08:49,916 --> 00:08:50,416
- So was I.
- [grunts]

189
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,083
Hmm.

190
00:08:55,166 --> 00:08:57,458
<i>They're gonna dock you points</i>
<i>for that hair.</i>

191
00:08:57,541 --> 00:09:00,000
All right.
Let's get cutting.

192
00:09:00,083 --> 00:09:01,500
- Hold up a sec.

193
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:04,333
Don't real barbers, like,
train how to do this?

194
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:05,833
- It'll be a cinch.

195
00:09:05,916 --> 00:09:08,541
I give little hair cuts
to myself all the time.

196
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,041
- This is more complicated
than trimming your bangs.

197
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:13,041
I'll go to a pro.
- As if!

198
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:15,208
You're gonna get lazy
and flake out!

199
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:16,458
Enough with the whining!

200
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:17,541
Time to man up

201
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,041
and kiss this
extra hair good-bye!

202
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:20,458
- This seems like a bad idea!

203
00:09:20,541 --> 00:09:22,541
[scissors snipping]

204
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:27,416
You're taking off more?
- Seriously, chill out.

205
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,541
Remember how I'd do this
when we were kids?

206
00:09:30,625 --> 00:09:32,375
[scissors snip]

207
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:35,625
The competition's coming up so
we gotta get you looking good.

208
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,416
- You make me sound like
a mess.

209
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,083
- Will Kao--
[gasps]

210
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,375
<i>Will Kaori be cheering you on?</i>

211
00:09:42,458 --> 00:09:44,083
<i>What does she think</i>
<i>of all this?</i>

212
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,166
<i>I wonder.</i>

213
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,541
<i>- Stop being so jealous</i>
<i>of music.</i>

214
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,916
<i>- I am, though.</i>
[scissors snip]

215
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,625
<i>I'm jealous that they</i>
<i>have music in common.</i>

216
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:59,500
<i>It's terrible,</i>
<i>but I can't help it.</i>

217
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:01,250
- Tsubaki?
- Hmm?

218
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:04,583
- I'm going to give this
my all.

219
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,916
Even if I go down
in flames out there,

220
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,541
I want you to know that.

221
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:10,750
- [gasps]

222
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,791
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

223
00:10:12,875 --> 00:10:16,166
Hmm.

224
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,750
[scissors snip]

225
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:19,250
<i>The dry snip of the scissors.</i>
[scissors snip]

226
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:22,500
<i>The tangle of his hair.</i>

227
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,000
<i>This moment is nothing at all,</i>

228
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:26,166
<i>and everything.</i>

229
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,625
Where's my rice ball?

230
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:31,166
- Uh, I thought they
were both for me.

231
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:34,291
<i>- Thanks for nothing, dummy!</i>
<i>- Ah!</i>

232
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:36,000
<i>- Whatever happens,</i>

233
00:10:36,083 --> 00:10:38,666
<i>I wouldn't trade our time</i>
<i>together for the world.</i>

234
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:40,958
<i>I hope he wouldn't, either.</i>

235
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:45,541
♪♪

236
00:10:57,541 --> 00:10:59,666
- I hope you're ready
for a workout.

237
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:00,791
- Well, you're even
a bit early.

238
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,125
Hold on.

239
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:06,000
Don't you wanna wait
for your friend to swing by?

240
00:11:06,083 --> 00:11:07,500
- I gave him the day off.

241
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:09,250
<i>It's for a good reason,</i>
<i>though.</i>

242
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:10,958
<i>Trust me.</i>

243
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:13,000
[piano music playing]

244
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:23,166
♪♪

245
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,791
- Has anybody seen Kashima?

246
00:11:24,875 --> 00:11:25,833
Entry number four?

247
00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:30,166
- Huh?

248
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:33,000
- Hmm.

249
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:35,500
- [snarls]

250
00:11:35,583 --> 00:11:37,458
- [whimpers]

251
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,791
Uh, you hungry?

252
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:42,000
- [chomps]

253
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:43,833
Mmm!

254
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:45,333
- Right?

255
00:11:45,416 --> 00:11:46,666
They go light on the mayo
and salt,

256
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:48,125
which really allows
the sweetness

257
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:48,750
of these free-range eggs
to shine through.

258
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,083
Wouldn't you say?

259
00:11:50,166 --> 00:11:52,458
It's not the only brand
of egg sandwich I'll eat,

260
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:53,458
but it's the only one
I'll recommend to others.

261
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:54,958
- [sighs]

262
00:11:55,041 --> 00:11:58,208
Man, nothing's coming up
but bile.

263
00:11:58,291 --> 00:11:59,708
Oh, what the hell?

264
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:00,791
- Hmm?

265
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:03,333
<i>- Emi and Arima?</i>

266
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:07,666
- Hmm.
- Huh?

267
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:12,583
Yeah, cool.
Whatever.

268
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:14,875
<i>I sure hope my stomach</i>
<i>can hack this.</i>

269
00:12:15,625 --> 00:12:17,000
[chomps]

270
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:18,583
Awesome!
- Right?

271
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:20,291
They go light on the mayo
and salt,

272
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:21,333
which really allows
the sweetness

273
00:12:21,416 --> 00:12:22,875
of these free-range eggs
to shine through.

274
00:12:22,958 --> 00:12:24,500
Wouldn't you say?

275
00:12:24,583 --> 00:12:25,958
It's not the only brand
of egg sandwich I'll eat,

276
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:27,666
but it's the only one
I'll recommend to others.

277
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:30,541
- A thick slice of ham
would make this even better.

278
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:33,250
- Especially when you've
got one with extra mayo.

279
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,166
- And some tea to wash it down.

280
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,291
- If you're paying,
make it a pork cutlet.

281
00:12:37,375 --> 00:12:38,583
- I could really go
for some florentines.

282
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:40,583
- I'm gonna hold out
for scones with my tea.

283
00:12:40,666 --> 00:12:42,750
- Best drink,
glass of milk.

284
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:44,500
- No, Darjeeling.
- Whoa.

285
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:47,416
They're really getting into it.
- Aren't they rivals?

286
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,416
- Number eight,
Takeshi Aiza.

287
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,291
Please take your place
in the wings.

288
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:52,833
- [groans]

289
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,458
Guess that's my cue to go.

290
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:02,291
I wish I could hit you
with some sick burn as I leave,

291
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:05,416
but I got nothing.

292
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:09,375
Maybe it's because all three
of us are pianists.

293
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:13,291
Yeah, we gotta say it
with music.

294
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:14,125
[both chuckling]

295
00:13:14,208 --> 00:13:17,166
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

296
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:18,833
♪♪

297
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:22,625
<i>Man, what a weird note</i>
<i>to leave on.</i>

298
00:13:22,708 --> 00:13:24,916
<i>Little chat,</i>
<i>little sandwich.</i>

299
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,625
<i>I'm calm as can be.</i>

300
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,583
<i>What if I'm too calm?</i>

301
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:31,791
<i>You guys are always getting</i>
<i>in my way somehow.</i>

302
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:33,791
[chuckles]

303
00:13:33,875 --> 00:13:36,125
♪♪

304
00:13:36,208 --> 00:13:39,791
- Here we go, then.

305
00:13:39,875 --> 00:13:41,500
- [exhales]

306
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:42,750
<i>You ready?</i>

307
00:13:44,875 --> 00:13:48,333
<i>Put everything out</i>
<i>of your mind.</i>

308
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:51,291
<i>Come on, Takeshi.</i>

309
00:13:51,375 --> 00:13:52,666
<i>You've got this!</i>

310
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:54,583
<i>Just play!</i>

311
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,916
♪♪

312
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,166
<i>Today I leave</i>
<i>those two behind!</i>

313
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:06,166
♪♪

314
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:09,416
[applause]

315
00:14:19,916 --> 00:14:20,500
<i>Back when I was a little kid,</i>

316
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:23,583
<i>I was such a spaz.</i>

317
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,541
<i>- Konnyaku?</i>
<i>- [laughing]</i>

318
00:14:26,625 --> 00:14:28,875
<i>- Giraffe class is gonna kick</i>
<i>all your butts!</i>

319
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:30,500
<i>- It's Takeshi!</i>
<i>Run, you guys!</i>

320
00:14:30,583 --> 00:14:32,000
<i>- [screaming]</i>

321
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:34,625
<i>My mom signed me up</i>
<i>for a bunch of lessons,</i>

322
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:38,041
<i>hoping something--anything</i>
<i>would command my attention</i>

323
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:40,541
<i>for more than five minutes.</i>

324
00:14:40,625 --> 00:14:42,041
<i>Turns out one</i>
<i>of those things...</i>

325
00:14:42,125 --> 00:14:43,541
<i>- Wow!</i>

326
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:45,666
<i>- Was the piano.</i>

327
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:47,625
<i>- You may need to find</i>
<i>a new instructor.</i>

328
00:14:47,708 --> 00:14:50,125
<i>I've run out of things</i>
<i>to teach him.</i>

329
00:14:50,208 --> 00:14:51,875
<i>- I get a new toy robot</i>
<i>if I win.</i>

330
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:54,791
<i>I guess I'd better win today,</i>
<i>huh?</i>

331
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:56,583
<i>[laughing]</i>

332
00:14:56,666 --> 00:14:57,833
<i>[grunts]</i>

333
00:14:57,916 --> 00:14:59,041
<i>Huh?</i>

334
00:14:59,125 --> 00:15:07,083
♪♪

335
00:15:07,166 --> 00:15:08,375
<i>Watch me.</i>

336
00:15:08,458 --> 00:15:11,541
<i>Emi,</i>
<i>Arima,</i>

337
00:15:11,625 --> 00:15:14,291
<i>I'm gonna blow past you</i>
<i>here and now.</i>

338
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,750
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Time to prove it!</i>

339
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:20,875
[piano music playing]

340
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:25,500
♪♪

341
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:29,625
<i>- Yes, Chopin's Etude,</i>
<i>Opus 10, Number 12.</i>

342
00:15:29,708 --> 00:15:32,625
<i>Go, Takeshi.</i>
<i>Go!</i>

343
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:34,625
<i>- Big brother.</i>

344
00:15:34,708 --> 00:15:36,416
<i>- I'm so lame.</i>

345
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,416
<i>This sucks.</i>

346
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:40,666
<i>Coming up short when I play.</i>

347
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,541
<i>Ignoring Nagi to the point</i>
<i>where she turns</i>

348
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:44,875
<i>to freaking Arima for help.</i>

349
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:47,583
<i>What the hell?</i>

350
00:15:47,666 --> 00:15:50,708
<i>It's like I'm a little kid</i>
<i>all over again!</i>

351
00:15:50,791 --> 00:15:53,250
<i>I can't believe I lost again!</i>

352
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,916
<i>- Brother, wait!</i>

353
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,625
<i>- How'd they beat me?</i>
<i>It doesn't make sense!</i>

354
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:58,166
[gasps]

355
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,416
<i>I'm way better at piano</i>
<i>than that cold-fish girl</i>

356
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,541
<i>and that sissy four-eyed</i>
<i>mama's boy!</i>

357
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:04,333
Damn it.

358
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:05,625
Damn it!

359
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:07,958
Damn it,
damn it!

360
00:16:08,041 --> 00:16:09,541
<i>Next time I'm gonna</i>
<i>beat them all!</i>

361
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:12,875
[screams]
- Wow.

362
00:16:12,958 --> 00:16:14,500
Look at him!

363
00:16:14,583 --> 00:16:16,916
He just ran up these stairs
like they were nothing.

364
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,666
He's so amazing!

365
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,958
- [gasping]

366
00:16:21,041 --> 00:16:24,333
[grunting]

367
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:26,208
[gasps]

368
00:16:26,291 --> 00:16:28,958
<i>How come I never</i>
<i>saw it before?</i>

369
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:30,958
<i>I thought I got you better</i>
<i>than anyone else,</i>

370
00:16:31,041 --> 00:16:33,500
<i>being rivals and all.</i>

371
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:36,791
<i>But then when I saw you</i>
<i>two years later...</i>

372
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:39,833
♪♪

373
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:41,791
<i>- You're not alone, though.</i>

374
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:43,666
<i>All of us</i>
<i>are in this together.</i>

375
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:45,666
<i>- I guess he finally found it.</i>

376
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:47,083
<i>A reason to play.</i>

377
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:50,666
<i>- I guess--I guess</i>
<i>that's who I am.</i>

378
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:53,041
<i>Right now that's all</i>
<i>I'm good for.</i>

379
00:16:53,125 --> 00:16:54,583
<i>- I think I kinda get it now.</i>

380
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:57,083
<i>It was always like this.</i>

381
00:16:57,166 --> 00:17:00,500
<i>I only reached the top</i>
<i>of the hill</i>

382
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:03,000
<i>because of you.</i>

383
00:17:03,083 --> 00:17:05,500
<i>You're back,</i>
<i>but you're a person now,</i>

384
00:17:05,583 --> 00:17:07,916
<i>full of surprises.</i>

385
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,583
<i>We're on a journey,</i>
<i>like you said,</i>

386
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:15,375
<i>but we're taking different</i>
<i>pictures along the way.</i>

387
00:17:15,458 --> 00:17:16,833
<i>Don't just play it.</i>

388
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,166
<i>Feel it.</i>

389
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:20,708
<i>Give it everything.</i>
<i>No choice!</i>

390
00:17:20,791 --> 00:17:24,875
♪♪

391
00:17:24,958 --> 00:17:26,875
<i>- He really wants to nail</i>
<i>today's performance.</i>

392
00:17:26,958 --> 00:17:30,458
<i>Honor the composer's</i>
<i>intention.</i>

393
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:32,208
<i>Give yourself over to it.</i>

394
00:17:32,291 --> 00:17:34,208
<i>Follow in the footsteps</i>
<i>of those who came before.</i>

395
00:17:34,291 --> 00:17:37,541
<i>Kousei Arima is a pretender</i>
<i>to the throne.</i>

396
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:39,541
<i>You, Takeshi Aiza,</i>

397
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:41,458
<i>are the heir</i>
<i>to this grand tradition.</i>

398
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,708
- [gasps]

399
00:17:43,791 --> 00:17:46,375
<i>Takeshi.</i>
<i>- He's a force of nature.</i>

400
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:48,166
<i>- Look at you.</i>

401
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:50,125
<i>Leaving nothing to</i>
<i>the imagination today, are we?</i>

402
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:53,833
<i>- Hmm, you've surpassed</i>
<i>your mentor, thankfully.</i>

403
00:17:53,916 --> 00:17:57,833
<i>He wouldn't know such pathos</i>
<i>if it bit him.</i>

404
00:17:57,916 --> 00:17:59,708
<i>- Go...</i>
<i>- One step...</i>

405
00:17:59,791 --> 00:18:01,791
<i>- In front of...</i>
<i>- Another!</i>

406
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,250
<i>- It's not just friends</i>
<i>who support each other.</i>

407
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:09,166
<i>The rival who gets under</i>
<i>your skin, priceless.</i>

408
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:11,708
<i>Knowing they're</i>
<i>out there fighting</i>

409
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:12,958
<i>the same lonely fight as you,</i>

410
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:16,708
<i>it's a comfort</i>
<i>and a fire under your ass.</i>

411
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:18,250
<i>They help each other,</i>

412
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:20,458
<i>even when they wanna punch</i>
<i>each other.</i>

413
00:18:20,541 --> 00:18:24,125
<i>- Two years now I've been</i>
<i>waiting for this day.</i>

414
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:26,875
<i>This moment that commands</i>
<i>my full attention.</i>

415
00:18:26,958 --> 00:18:28,791
<i>I can smash into this piece</i>
<i>with everything.</i>

416
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:31,916
<i>I'm not gonna lose next time!</i>

417
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,416
<i>Next time I'm gonna</i>
<i>demolish you both!</i>

418
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:37,916
♪♪

419
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,750
<i>I hit these guys</i>
<i>with everything I've got</i>

420
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,541
<i>and they don't even flinch.</i>

421
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:46,458
♪♪

422
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:49,458
<i>Damn, I'm lucky.</i>

423
00:18:57,875 --> 00:18:59,958
<i>- Just like that,</i>

424
00:19:00,041 --> 00:19:02,166
<i>my hero returns.</i>

425
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,750
[cheers and applause]

426
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:07,875
- Bravo!
- He's never been better!

427
00:19:08,583 --> 00:19:11,208
- [shuddering]

428
00:19:11,291 --> 00:19:12,458
- Big brother!

429
00:19:12,541 --> 00:19:13,666
[gasps]

430
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:15,208
<i>I gotta cheer</i>
<i>for Takeshi of course,</i>

431
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:16,875
<i>but Arima's competing, too.</i>

432
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:17,875
<i>Can I cheer for them both?</i>
<i>What do I do?</i>

433
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:21,083
<i>This is such a cliché!</i>

434
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:23,500
<i>- Looks like somebody decided</i>
<i>to bring his A-game.</i>

435
00:19:23,583 --> 00:19:26,833
- [chuckles]

436
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:29,791
<i>You did Chopin proud, boy.</i>

437
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:33,458
<i>Good job.</i>
- Uh, guys?

438
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:36,750
I still have one more number
to play.

439
00:19:38,958 --> 00:19:41,208
[screams]
- [gasps]

440
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:42,458
- [breathing heavily]

441
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:43,833
- Excellent work.
- Yeah, no kidding.

442
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,666
Especially the Chopin.

443
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:48,625
What was up with
my second song?

444
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:50,583
It felt like a whole
'nother room.

445
00:19:50,666 --> 00:19:53,666
- That's what you get
for blowing all their minds.

446
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:57,458
- You should have wrapped up
with the Chopin piece instead.

447
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:59,833
- [gasps]

448
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:02,500
<i>Did I reach them?</i>

449
00:20:02,583 --> 00:20:05,333
<i>Was I able to reach them</i>
<i>with my music?</i>

450
00:20:07,166 --> 00:20:08,666
<i>Like you guys do?</i>

451
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:11,208
[grunts]
- Whoa!

452
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:12,583
- Don't even think
of wussing out this time!

453
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:14,625
You gotta make it to the finals
so I can beat you then!

454
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:16,458
both: Hmm.

455
00:20:16,541 --> 00:20:17,083
- [grunts]

456
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,875
- If you make it.

457
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:20,583
That second song was shaky.

458
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:21,666
- What?

459
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:24,041
- You might wanna dial down
on the bravado.

460
00:20:24,125 --> 00:20:25,833
That kinda stuff can really
come back to bite you.

461
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:27,458
- [grunts]
Who asked you, Arima?

462
00:20:27,541 --> 00:20:30,666
Hey, you better not put
the moves on my sister!

463
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:33,458
- Why would I do that?
- Why wouldn't you do that?

464
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:35,125
You saying Nagi's ugly
or something?

465
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:37,916
[gasping]

466
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:42,041
<i>Arima, I can never say it,</i>

467
00:20:42,125 --> 00:20:45,041
<i>but I owe this all to you.</i>

468
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:47,916
<i>My rival,</i>
<i>my hero.</i>

469
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:51,208
<i>Thank you for everything.</i>

470
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:56,583
- There are the results!

471
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:58,416
- My name!
I see it!

472
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:59,416
- Really?

473
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,458
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

474
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:05,125
♪♪

475
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:06,083
<i>- [grunts]</i>

476
00:21:06,166 --> 00:21:07,416
<i>What a bunch of noobs.</i>

477
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:11,041
<i>- Arima's sitting</i>
<i>right next to me.</i>

478
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:20,875
♪♪

479
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:23,916
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

